verbose_text: NF-kappaB p65 nuclear translocation was quantified by imaging flow cytometry, using the similarity feature (XREF_FIG A, representative images of B cells and monocytes in XREF_FIG B), demonstrating that nuclear translocation of p65 was strongest in the T/T genotype at rs140490 for both CD40L stimulated B cells and TNF stimulated monocytes.
